name: Paolini
summary: American tennis player Madison Keys has withdrawn from Wimbledon due to a leg injury, allowing Italian Jasmine Paolini to advance to the quarterfinals. Paolini's victory marks a significant milestone for Italian women's tennis, as she becomes the first Italian woman to reach the round of 16 in the first three Grand Slams of the season. Her victory over Keys was particularly emotional, as Keys was forced to retire during the third set after suffering an injury. Paolini's advancement to the quarterfinals sets the stage for a potential match-up against Coco Gauff, who was recently defeated by Emma Navarro, or Jelena Ostapenko.

name: Khyree Jackson
summary: Tragically, Minnesota Vikings rookie cornerback Khyree Jackson has passed away in a Maryland car crash. The 24-year-old was traveling with two former high school teammates when the incident occurred. Jackson, a former Oregon cornerback, was a promising player for the Vikings who had started four games in his first NFL season. Authorities have provided details surrounding the accident, including images of the crash scene. The accident has deeply impacted the Vikings organization, who have released a statement expressing their condolences and support for Jackson's family. News outlets have widely reported on this devastating event, highlighting Jackson's promising career and the tragic circumstances of his passing.

name: Netherlands vs Turkey
summary: The Netherlands secured a thrilling 2-1 victory over Turkey in the Euro 2024 quarter-finals, advancing to the semi-finals where they will face England. The match, which was played on July 6, 2024, saw the Dutch come back from behind to secure the win. Turkey had taken the lead through a first-half goal, but the Netherlands equalized in the second half and grabbed the winner in the dying minutes. The victory sent the Netherlands through to the semi-finals, while Turkey's Euro 2024 campaign came to an end.
